title: Tim
body:
<<if visited ("Tim") is false and if visited ("Steve") is false>>
Norra: Hi!
Tim: Hello, Norra. 
Tim: Are you looking for something to do? 
Tim: Steve is working to clear some fallen trees off the path.
Tim: He's out in the lower forest, and the chainsaw is broken. 
Tim: Can you bring him the axe so he can finish clearing the paths?
<<elseif visited ("Tim") is false and if visited ("Steve") is true>>
Tim: Hello, Norra.
Norra: Hi Tim!
Norra: Steve sent me up here. 
Norra: He said the chainsaw is broken
Norra: and he needs the axe so he can finish clearing the paths. 
Tim: Okay, the axe is in the toolshed. 
Tim: I'll unlock it for you.
<<elseif visited ("Tim") is true>>
Tim: Steve is still waiting for that axe. . . 
<<endif>>
